The Southwest Agenda for Asiwaju (SWAGA) will on Wednesday holds a symposium for youth. Tagged: The Lagos Youth Symposium, the symposium, with theme, Youth Political Participation: Driving Youth Engagement and inclusivity in Governance through political involvement will hold the Abibatu Mogaji Memorial Hall in Coker-Aguda Local Council Development Area secretariat. Director of Planning and Strategy, SWAGA Lagos Youth directorate, Afis Olaseinde Kasumu, said that the nation’s development is hinged on how competent youths are identified, in leadership roles. He said robust discussions would be made concerning the 2023 elections and how it would propel the emergence of the best candidates.   SDP, APC disagree over attack on Oni’s running mate     Deputy Speaker hails APC congress     Our achievements will give us victory, says Oyetola   According to Kasumu, Nigerians should be guided by the principles that births economic transformation which is hinged on youth political participation, engagement and inclusion in governance ‘. “What we are trying to obtain from this symposium is also to identify factors that are militating against youth participation in governance and politics,” he said. Chairman of Coker-Aguda Local Council Development Area, Rasaq Ibrahim, urged All Progressives Congress (APC) to elect Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu as the party’s flagbearer for 2023 presidential election. He said: “Asiwaju Tinubu has the capacity to take Nigeria to greater heights. We do have different needs but the person that can address our needs is Asiwaju Tinubu. Again, people should go and get their Permanent Voter’s Card (PVC). That is their power.“